  "source": "claude-advisor",
  "edge_hypothesis": "Vortex crossovers are the proven alpha source — v3a PF=2.034 across ALL regimes, transitional PF=3.886. But raw Vortex generates some false crossovers during choppy price action. T3 (Tillson triple-smoothed EMA) is the smoothest available moving average — it filters micro-noise that causes premature Vortex crosses. By requiring Vortex crossover to ALIGN with T3 trend direction (close vs T3), we filter false transitions while preserving the genuine regime-change signals that make Vortex profitable. No regime gate needed — Vortex family profits across all regimes, so adding CHOP would only reduce trade count without improving PF.",
